05015nam a2200601Ia 9781526168436DE-B159720240426104009.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240426t20232023xxk    fo  d z      eng d  a97815261684367 a10.7765/97815261684362doi  a(DE-B1597)680053  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  axxkcGB 7aSOC0260002bisacsh04aThe photographs of Zygmunt Bauman /ced. by Peter Beilharz, Janet Wolff. 1aManchester : bManchester University Press, c[2023] 4cÂ©2023  a1 online resource (152 p.) :b77 black & white illustrations  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFront Matter -- tContents -- tIntroduction -- t1 Figures, images, spaces -- t2 Pictures in words, words in pictures (2010) -- t3 The war against forgetfulness (1989) -- t4 Praxis, time, seeing -- t5 Captured by Zygmunt -- t6 Janina Bauman in Film Polski -- t7 Bauman and Tester at the movies -- t8 Bauman and Bergman -- t9 Gazing sociologically, thinking photographically, deciphering gender -- t10 Smoke-filled rooms -- tAcknowledgements -- tContributors -- tNotes on photographs -- tPlates0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2fd2star  aZygmunt Bauman is known internationally as the sociologist of postmodernity and 'liquid' society. But he was also a serious photographer. This book presents a selection of his black-and-white photographs, together with a range of essays by colleagues, friends and family about his work with images.The book features a mixture of short pieces on individual photographs and longer essays addressing aspects of Bauman's photography and the life and work of his wife, Janina. These include an essay of Bauman's from 1989, in which he considers Monika Krajewska's photographs of abandoned Jewish graveyards in Poland. Also reprinted is an essay by Bauman's daughter Lydia, taken from the catalogue of an exhibition of the photographs in 2010, and an essay by Keith Tester about Bauman's interest in film. Jack Palmer discusses the relationship between Bauman's sociology and his photography, while Peter Beilharz, Janet Wolff, and Antony Bryant and Griselda Pollock offer personal reflections on some of Bauman's photographs. The book concludes with an essay by Karl Dudman, one of the Baumans' grandchildren, based on a series of photographs he took in the family home shortly after his grandfather's death.Janina Bauman appears in a number of ways in the book. Some of the photographs are of her, and several of the short essays discuss her place in Zygmunt's life and work. Izabela Wagner, biographer of Zygmunt Bauman, presents new material on Janina's work in the Polish film industry in the post-war period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh1 aBauman, Lydia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBauman, Zygmunt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeilharz, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeilharz, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBryant, Antony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDudman, Karl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPalmer, Jack, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPollock, Griselda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTester, Keith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWagner, Izabela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWolff, Janet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWolff, Janet, eeditor.